# mms dev-jar overlay list — repo slugs currently under active testing.
#
# One repo slug per line (the folder name under ~/Documents/GitHub/). Its newest
# build/libs/*.jar is dropped onto the test server + test client on top of the
# pack, replacing the released version by Fabric mod id. This is the ONLY place
# an unreleased build lives — it is deliberately not tracked in the pack index.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Add a slug here while you iterate on that mod.
#   2. Build the jar, run ./mms-deploy-test.sh, test on MMSTesting01 with two
#      offline clients.
#   3. Once validated, PROMOTE: remove the slug from this list, then run the
#      normal ./mms-deploy.sh (cuts the GitHub release, updates main, syncs
#      MMSLive01). The mod re-enters the pack at its released version.
#
# Example (uncomment while testing the next metro fix):
# mms-mod-compat-support
